  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Group Finance Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong><br /><br />Reporting to the Group CEO and Group Finance Director, the incumbent shall be responsible for:-</p><ul><li>Supervise group finance team in the timely preparation of monthly and annual consolidation of financial reports for management and statutory reporting purposes</li><li>Analyse, measure and monitor performance of subsidiaries; make recommendations for improvements.</li><li>Assist in treasury matters, including monthly reporting of cash balances across the regions.</li><li>Coordinate with the subsidiaries in the preparation of annual budget and financial plans; challenge their assumptions and drive performance.</li><li>Provide IFRS accounting support to the subsidiaries and conduct finance training for the Group</li><li>Implement financial and accounting policies and procedures for the Group.  Ensure compliance with good governance, practice and standards</li><li>Liaise with bankers for all corporate banking matters and external auditors for year-end audit</li><li>Implement Group reporting system</li><li>Any other ad hoc improvements projects</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Possess Bachelor Degree in Accountancy or ACCA</li><li>At least 6 years of experience in similar capacity</li><li>Strong knowledge in IFRS/SFRS accounting</li><li>Strong analytical, numerical and meticulous skills required</li><li>Excellent interpersonal and communication skills</li><li>Good organizational skills and with a focus on meeting deadlines</li><li>Committed, self-motivated and proactive</li><li>Proficient in MS Excel</li></ul><p></p>",
